e OTP input behavior, specifically addressing backspace key functionality and focus management. The goal is to make sure pressing backspace properly clears and navigates, allowing for a smooth and intuitive user experience. I'm also ensuring the code triggers a verification process once all six digits are entered.\n\n\n**Initializing OTP for Previews**\n\nI've just added logic to initialize the OTP code when a user selects a role in the sandbox preview. This will pre-populate the digit boxes with the values from the mock user data, specifically setting the OTP code to \"102486\" when `selectedRole` changes. The user can then interact with this state to complete the preview. I've also implemented the copy/paste functionality.\n\n\n**Rendering OTP Value**\n\nI'm now ensuring the six individual inputs correctly render the OTP code digits: `otpCode[0]` through `otpCode[5]`. They will render the values and advance focus on input. I'm also adding a \"Simulated Rotating MFA Code\" countdown timer. I've included a React hook and logic, and the code should update the input in the correct intervals, as shown in the example code. I'm making sure this simulated timer resets, logs the event, and updates the state.\n\n\n**Simulating Code Rotation**\n\nI'm now implementing the simulated TOTP rotation alongside the countdown. I've designed the countdown to reset to 30 seconds and generate a new mock code when the timer hits zero, ensuring the code is visible in the telemetry log. To enhance user immersion in the sandbox preview, the code will remain as `102486` if the role is switched.\n\n```\n```\n\n**Crafting Visual Enhancements**\n\nI'm now integrating an animated SVG token countdown ring, and the current code is working seamlessly to give it a high-tech custom feel. It feels incredibly premium. I'm shifting focus to the \"Forgot Passphrase Key Recovery\" flow, specifically the UI for the \"Simulation Vector Confirmed\" stage; I want it to be exceptionally polished.\n\n\n**Designing Recovery Visualization**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in designing a multi-step recovery sequence. I'm focusing on an animated \"Handshake Isolation Sequence\" with visual steps: Verification Node Handshake, Dynamic Recovery Crypt-Token, and Out-of-band Delivery Pipeline. I want to create a compelling SVG graphic to visualize the \"Secure Recovery Transmission Vector,\" illustrating the connection between user node, crypt node, and out-of-band email enclave. The goal is a captivating, elegant UI.\n\n\n**Visualizing Connection Dynamics**\n\nI'm now drafting an SVG graphic, intending it to show moving, glowing dots along paths, symbolizing simulated packets in a zero-trust enclave. This visual metaphor will illustrate the connection. I'm focusing on crafting this elegant UI with CSS and SVG elements, specifically the \"Handshake Isolation Sequence.\"\n\n\n**Visualizing Connection Dynamics**\n\nI'm now drafting an SVG graphic to represent the recovery connection. I'm focusing on glowing dots moving along paths to simulate secure data packets within a zero-trust enclave, aiming for elegance through CSS and SVG elements, specifically for the \"Handshake Isolation Sequence.\"\n\n\n**Refining Keyframe Integration**\n\nI'm now incorporating custom CSS keyframes for the SVG animation to achieve full self-containment. My focus is ensuring the animation is bulletproof and works flawlessly without external dependencies. I'm choosing either inline styles or custom utility classes within the React component. I'm also reviewing existing global CSS to prevent duplication and ensure a clean, optimized implementation.\n\n\n"}}
